The paper deals with improving OCR text obtained from OCRopus models trained on early printed books. This involves techniques related to image processing, computer vision, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) which deals with techniques for searching and retrieving information from large datasets. The paper also involves techniques related to computer vision (cs.CV) such as image processing and feature extraction. Additionally, the paper involves deep learning (cs.DL) techniques for training the OCRopus models. The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques for processing the OCR text. Finally, the paper involves techniques related to machine learning (cs.LG) for building and training the OCRopus models.
